1. The proportion of patients experiencing nausea at 2 hours was 38.2% in the colloid group.
2. The proportion of patients experiencing nausea at 2 hours was 17.9% in the crystalloid group.
3. The proportion of patients experiencing nausea was significantly higher in the colloid group compared to the crystalloid group at 2 hours (P = 0.03).
4. The mean nausea score at 2 hours in the colloid group was 1.49 ± 0.3.
5. The mean nausea score at 2 hours in the crystalloid group was 0.68 ± 0.2.
6. The mean nausea score was significantly higher in the colloid group compared to the crystalloid group at 2 hours (P = 0.028).
